# Initial Access

## Overview

The **Initial Access** tactic covers techniques adversaries use to gain an initial foothold within a target environment. Successful initial access enables attackers to execute malicious code, establish persistence, and continue through the attack lifecycle.

This section contains Splunk detection use cases designed to identify suspicious authentication attempts, remote access activity, and exploitation techniques commonly associated with initial compromise.

