## Planned Detections

### Detection 1: Multiple Failed Logins

Detect repeated failed authentication attempts that may indicate password spraying or brute-force attacks.

---

### Detection 2: Successful Login After Multiple Failures

Identify accounts that successfully authenticate immediately after multiple failed login attempts.

---

### Detection 3: Suspicious RDP Authentication

Detect Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) logins originating from unusual hosts, external IP addresses, or outside normal business hours.

---

### Detection 4: Suspicious SMB Authentication

Identify unusual SMB authentication activity that may indicate unauthorized access attempts or lateral movement.

---

### Detection 5: VPN Login From New Location

Detect VPN logins originating from previously unseen geographic locations or IP ranges.

